Introduction

SAY MY NAME is a seven-member South Korean girl group under iNKODE.

On August 29, 2024, iNKODE confirmed plans to debut its first-ever idol group in October, with veteran singer Kim Jae Joong heavily involved in the group's development and training.

The next day, on August 30, the group's name and first member, Dohee, were revealed. From then on until September 13, the members were announced every two or three days. The second member, Kanny, was revealed on September 2, follower by Mei on September 4, Junhwi on September 6, Soha on September 9, Seungjoo on September 11, and Hitomi on September 13.

Prior to the group, Hitomi was known for being a member of the Japanese girl group AKB48, as well as a contestant on MNET's survival show Produce 48 and its final group, IZ*ONE, Mei for being a contestant on HYBE x Geffen Records' survival show Dream Academy, and Seungjoo for being a contestant on MBC's survival show My Teenage Girl.

SAY MY NAME debuted on October 16, 2024 with the release of their first mini album "SAY MY NAME".
